===Adjective===
'''new'''  ({{compar}}: '''[[newer]]''', {{superl}}: '''[[newest]]''')
# [[recently|Recently]] [[made]], [[created]], [[arrived]], [[appeared]], [[discovered]], [[experienced]], [[emerged]] or [[acquired]]
#: ''This is a '''new''' scratch on my car!''
#: ''She is the '''new '''kid at school''
#: ''My sister has a '''new''' baby''
# [[current|Current]] or [[later]], as opposed to [[former]].
#: ''My '''new''' car is much better than my previous one, even though it is older.''
#: ''We ad been in our '''new''' house for five years by then.''
# Used to distinguish something established more recently, [[named after]] something or some place previously existing.
#: '''''New''' Bond Street is an extension of Bond Street.''
#: '''''New''' York is named after York.''
# In [[original]] [[condition]]; not previously worn or used.''
#: ''Are you going to buy a '''new''' car or a second-hand one.''
#<strike> Different; clean; dry.
#:<strike> ''Put on '''new''' socks.''
# [[refresh|Refreshed]], [[reinvigorat]]ed, [[reform]]ed
#: ''That shirt is dirty. Go and put on a '''new''' one.''
#: ''I feel like a '''new''' person after a good night's sleep.''
#: ''He started a '''new''' life after leaving prison.''
# [[strange|Strange]], [[unfamiliar]] or not previously [[experience]]d
#: ''The idea was '''new''' to me.
#: ''I'm '''new''' at this business.''

